annotation.TEXT: Pfft, nice jump.
Oh, but fortunately, those falling fireballs aren't actually hurting me! However, I'm certain the Bowser statue's fireballs are just as harmful as usual!
I like how I was able to allow the "Go Go Go!" music to complete one loop.
There's a little bit of left+right assistance there, but I'm not going to break the level with that glitch. I just wanted to get the Yoshi coin a little faster.
23 coins is sure as heck better than the 3 coins I got from that multi-coin block last time!
Anyways, let me try for that moon again, and hopefully land on the message box properly this time...
Now, there seems to be a land formation pointing up here...
And now to do most of that again, but faster!
Miss!
There we go. I knew you could do it, Mario!
Let's see if I can hit the balloon block from here...
D'oh, I missed! Oh, I guess that's where the P-switch gets used.
Abandoned House
I think I'll wait on the multi-coin block until after I've done my ballooning this time.
And now for the usual ludicrously sped up bonus game.
The sky is on fire!
So, I have these five levels left to do, but which one should I play next?
And red is the winner! So, that means my next destination will be The sky is on fire!
Okay, that's four Yoshi coins, so I might be close to the end of the level...
Oh, man. So much lag...
BGM: Lunar Silver Star Story Complete - Go Go Go!
So, which of these levels will I be playing next? Vote now, and we'll find out next time!
Okay, so these clouds lead to where I've already been, so that little shortcut I took earlier wasn't really necessary.
A key? Nuts. I was hoping for a vine, but I guess that would've made the moon too easy to reach.
Super Pipe Town
Oh, come on! Seriously? That stupid statue jumped to just the right height at just the right time to trigger that stupid "ascending" glitch on me? GRR!!!
Wait, did I just see...?
No, I'm up to 8000, but there's nothing else nearby to stomp! Nuts.
I can certainly spin jump ride this fireball backwards, though!
Umm... I'm going to assume for now that that Yoshi coin was all that the balloon is used for.
Amazeing Grass Cave
To be continued...
Man, is every fire-themed enemy going to be present in this level? Even the red koopas could be considered fire-themed... if I had a Yoshi that didn't have to be incinerated.
Looks like it's used for a Yoshi coin, but is there anything else?
Red's at 8000, so one more red hit wins it!
Ooh, there's a springboard! I know what I'm doing with it!
MOOOOOOOONNNNN!!!!!!!

There we go. Now, while the hopping flame is slide-killable, the little embers it leaves behind aren't, and will still burn you. Also, I don't think the Bowser statue's fire can be slide-killed either.
Whoa! It's raining fireballs!
Gah! Screwed up while trying to slide-kill that hopping flame...
Whoa! I somehow missed the clouds I was aiming for there! Good thing I landed on something solid!
Huh, a P-switch. I wonder if I should stomp it now or later... I'll choose later, and if I'm wrong... Well, I'll have to play this level at least twice anyway.
I'm surprised I landed safely after that last moon jump attempt.
Oh, can I get a 1-up combo going here?

Same rules as usual. First shell to get a 1-up wins! Also, I've set this room to have no music this time so that I can let the "Go Go Go!" music keep playing. Oh, and the left shell = Super Pipe Town, and the right shell = The sky is on fire!
Nuts! Not quite... Maybe I need a springboard or something...
Let's try to do that jump better this time!
I was intending to burn that shell, but putting out a fire with it works even better for me!
Hey there dudes, and welcome back to another exciting episode of Inappropriate Jetski 19!
Barf. That wasn't very good.
Whoa! Almost got torched there.
Heh, there were so many sprites that the message box failed to spawn there. Good thing that the MOOOONNN is an object and not a sprite!
Nuts, you can't shell-kill the hopping statues either. Well, it didn't hurt to try.
I certainly would've done better on this multi-coin block if the balloon didn't change my priorities. Now, as for this springboard...
Super Pipe Town
Diggin' a mole hole
What? You can't slide-kill the hopping Bowser statues? You could in the original SMW! Dang it, patgangster! Why'd you have to change them to be un-slide-killable?
Alright, so let's see just how "on fire" the sky is!
Ooh, I can bounce up here.
Alright, duders! There's four levels left! Let's take a quick look at their names again...
Moon count: 1
Found the keyhole, and another Yoshi coin. Hmm... I don't know how much longer the level is, and I'm getting low on time, so I'll just take the secret exit now.
Well, let's see what the viewers have decided for me this time...
A balloon? I'd better deal with that first, since the springboard's not going anywhere.
The fiery rain is screaming "SomeGuy712x"? That's some really weird rain.

What the...? Oh, yeah. That's right. The same sprite slot issue that affects whether or not I can shell-kill Thwimps also affects hopping flames. I'd still like to know why Nintendo programmed it that way...
MUST HAVE!!! GIMME! GIMME! GIMME! Maybe I can reach it with a max speed jump from the message box...

Oh, and the last Yoshi coin and goal were right here, so I didn't have far to go at all! If I had known how close to the goal I was, I probably would've gotten the normal exit first. Oh, well. Either way, I would've had to go through most of the level twice.
